In order to install the nuFFTW library, follow these steps:

1. Download the source files from this link
https://www.dropbox.com/sh/atohxw3v41ryveq/iX8quXKqGn
Click Download -> Download as .zip.

This can also be done via the terminal by:
For Linux:
wget -O /path/to/downloadfolder/nuFFTW.zip "https://dl.dropboxusercontent.com/shz/atohxw3v41ryveq/iX8quXKqGn/nuFFTW?token_hash=AAEOAJGF_vKNuhG7X0ut2V94eHfaqJ6O17aAQXGW-Mj6_A&top_level_offset=7"
For Mac:
curl -o /path/to/downloadfolder/nuFFTW.zip "https://dl.dropboxusercontent.com/shz/atohxw3v41ryveq/iX8quXKqGn/nuFFTW?token_hash=AAEOAJGF_vKNuhG7X0ut2V94eHfaqJ6O17aAQXGW-Mj6_A&top_level_offset=7"

2. Unpack nuFFTW.zip wherever you would like the nuFFTW library to reside.
From the terminal this can be done by
unzip /path/to/downloadfolder/nuFFTW.zip -d /path/to/nufftwinstallfolder

3. Run the install.sh script from a terminal:
cd /path/to/nufftwinstallfolder
./install.sh
This will download and build the fftw and oski libraries, and build the nuFFTW binaries.


